election_record.label: New York 1824 Governor

sub_unit.name: Richmond
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 356 votes as Samuel Youngs.

sub_unit.name: Suffolk
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 1 vote for S. Young and 1 vote as Col. Young.

sub_unit.name: Westchester
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 4 votes as Samuel Youngs.

sub_unit.name: Albany
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 1 vote as S. Young and 1 vote as Samuel S. Young.

sub_unit.name: Schoharie
sub_unit.note: DeWitt Clinton received 1 vote as De Witt.

sub_unit.name: Essex
sub_unit.note: DeWitt Clinton received 1 vote as Lit Clinton.

sub_unit.name: Montgomery
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 2 votes as S. Young, 2 votes as Young and 1 vote as S. A. Young.

sub_unit.name: Saint Lawrence
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 68 votes as Samuel Youngs.

sub_unit.name: Lewis
sub_unit.note: DeWitt Clinton received 3 votes as DeWitt Clinlon.

sub_unit.name: Steuben
sub_unit.note: The votes as given in the Annals and Recollections of Oneida County, for the town of Steuben - DeWitt Clinton 49 and Rufus Young 116, were apparently not included in the State Wide Official Canvass of votes. There is nothing indicating that it was rejected or missing. For some reason, when the returns were transcribed and sent to Albany, the votes for this town apparently were not included and officials in Albany, unless told, would probably have no idea it was missing. There were 22 towns in Oneida County and officials in Albany may not have noticed if one was missing in the return.

sub_unit.name: Chenango
sub_unit.note: The November 24, 1824 edition of the Oxford Gazette (Oxford, NY) had DeWitt Clinton receiving 2137 votes instead of 2139.

sub_unit.name: Caroline
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 143 votes as Samuel Youngs.

sub_unit.name: Onondaga
sub_unit.note: DeWitt Clinton received 1 vote as Ewitt Clinton.

sub_unit.name: Seneca
sub_unit.note: In Seneca County, Samuel Young was listed as a King Caucus Candidate while DeWitt Clinton was affiliated with the People's Ticket.

sub_unit.name: Cattaraugus
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 6 votes as Samuel Youngs.

sub_unit.name: Erie
sub_unit.note: The Albany Argus (Albany, NY) and Michael Dubin reported that Samuel Young received 871 votes in Erie.
Samuel Young received 1 vote as Samuel Yang.

sub_unit.name: Steuben
sub_unit.note: Samuel Young received 1 vote as Samuel Youngs and 1 vote as Samuel Yongs.
